      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, what happened there? the last paragraph is getting really weird. \"pre-approved dormancy area\" and \"escapist surroundings\"? it sounds like a sci-fi novel, not an employee handbook. the score definitely went up, but this is definitely not \"clear and professional\" like I asked for. it's actually getting harder to understand what the actual steps are because of all the extra fluff.\n\ncan you try one more time? please, just focus on the actual instructions. use strong verbs to keep the score up, but strip out all that weird, dramatic filler. i need it to be a normal, boring, easy-to-follow guide for a new hire.",
